Project Name: Minimal Restrained Blog
Goal: Ship a production-ready, extremely fast static blog today with 4 pages only.
Architecture: Next.js 15 App Router + Tailwind CSS + MDX blog posts
Performance target: 100/100 Lighthouse on mobile & desktop, < 50 KB JS, < 1 second LCP
Design philosophy: Maximum restraint
  - Typography: 2 type sizes max (base 18px, headings 32px or 40px)
  - Colors: 2 colors max (#000000 and #ffffff, or #111111 + #fafafa if needed)
  - Fonts: System stack only (-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Helvetica, sans-serif)
  - No images except one optional tiny logo.svg
  - No icons, no illustrations, no rounded corners, no shadows, no hover effects beyond underline
  - Monolithic, brutalist-minimal feel — think early 2010s Tumblr but perfectly executed
Pages needed (exact 4):
  - Home / Blog index (list of 4 articles)
  - Individual blog post page (MDX)
  - /about
  - /careers
  - /contact (simple form + email link, no backend needed)
Deployment: Vercel (one-click from Cursor)
Content: All content lives in MDX files inside /app/blog/posts/ — no CMS, no database
Styling: Global CSS with exactly one stylesheet, Tailwind used only for utilities (no custom config beyond base colors)
Build constraints:
  - Use Next.js static export where possible (ISR only for blog posts if needed)
  - No client-side JavaScript except what's required for MDX hydration
  - Zero runtime JS on about/careers/contact pages
Tone: Serious, quiet, confident, restrained